      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Take heed that no man lead you astray",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Greek word is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "πλανήση",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Their first temptation would be of this kind - that many would come in Christ's name, saying, \"I am he;\" claiming, that is, the title which belonged to him alone. Such were Theudas (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 5:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and Simon Magus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), who, according to Jerome, said, \"Ego sum Sermo Dei, ego speciosus, ego Paracletus, ego omnipotens, ego omnia.\" Such were Menander and the Gnostics. Mark 13:5",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
